ANNs can well enable arbitrarily complex non-stationary series to obtain any desired accuracy thanks to its flexible nonlinear mapping ability52. The NARANN method with the time-varying state of interconnected neurons is an important dynamic recurrent ANNs model. For this reason, this method has the inherent attributes of ANNs (e.g., powerful nonlinear mapping capacity, self-learning and adaption ability, along with generalization and fault-tolerant ability)33,53. Further, the NARANN model also has a long or short-term memory function by retaining the prior inputs, outputs and network structures with the help of the tapped delay line, resulting in a dynamic modeling potential to the time-dependent series33. An NARANN method can be in the form below1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
